Introduction to the dataset -

IMDB is the online database of information

IMDB is a internet Database largest databases for TV and movies.

The dataset contains the top rated movies on IMDB for the year 2021, it provides details of the popular and high rated movies. Analyzing the trends and popular genres from the dataset.

Features of the data are movie title, ratings, tagline, budget, box office, certificate, run time, director, name, votes, casts, writers and year of release.

  • Genres has categorical data which includes dram, action, comedy, adventure, horror, biography, science and romance styles.

  • Ratings are provided from 1 to 10 scale

  • Certificates are the rating provided by the certification board

Creating and Ploting Word Cloud

In [104]:
from wordcloud import STOPWORDS as stopwords_wc
from wordcloud import ImageColorGenerator, WordCloud

all_genre = " ".join(spoken for spoken in movies_data["genre"])
stopwords_wc = set(stopwords_wc)

wording = WordCloud(stopwords = stopwords_wc,
                      max_font_size = 400,
                      random_state = 52, max_words = 1400,
                      width = 1900, height = 900, 
                      background_color = 'white')
wording.generate(all_genre)

plt.figure(figsize = (18, 9))
plt.axis("off")
plt.imshow(wording)
plt.show();

According to the above Word Cloud representation, all the genres are displayed in a better visualization of text data into pattern

1. Which Genre movies has the highest movie ratings?¶

In [36]:
top_rating = movies_data.groupby('genre').mean().sort_values('rating',ascending=False).head(5)
top_rating = top_rating[['rating']].round(2)
top_rating.reset_index(inplace=True)
top_rating
data_figure = px.violin(movies_data, x='genre', y='rating', color='genre', title='Highest Movie Ratings according to Genre')
data_figure.show()

Summary :

From the above violin plot, it is observed that Drama, Crime, Action, Biography and History are the highest 5 Genres populated from the dataset.

2. What are the top 10 movies recommendation according to Ratings?¶

In [96]:
top_genre = movies_data.sort_values(by='rating', ascending=False).head(10)
In [84]:
top_ratings = movies_data.nlargest(10, 'rating')
fig = go.Figure(data=[go.Bar(x = top_ratings['name'], y = top_ratings['rating'], marker = {'color': '#dba506'})])
fig.update_layout(title = 'Top 10 Movies recommendation considering Rating')
fig.show()

Summary :

From the above Bar plot, 'The Shawshank Redemption' is the most rated movie which is populated from the dataset.

4. Which director has the most movies on the list?¶

In [94]:
gen_year = movies_data.pivot_table(index='directors', columns='year', values='rating', aggfunc='mean')
figure_data = px.imshow(gen_year, color_continuous_scale = 'Reds', 
                 title = ' Highest Movie count directed by director')
figure_data.update_layout(xaxis_title = '-Year-', yaxis_title = '-Directors-')
figure_data.show()

Summary :

According to the above pivot table plotting, it is observed that Christopher Nolan has the highest count of movies directed in year 2018.
